  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "M&E Technician Cum Mechanical Engineer",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>Lead and manage technical teams handling plant maintenance, equipment servicing, and building maintenance works.</li><li>Oversee 24/7 breakdown support operations and ensure rapid response for critical plant issues.</li><li>Plan, coordinate and supervise maintenance schedules, shutdown works, and project deployments.</li><li>Conduct site inspections, identify technical problems and provide effective engineering solutions.</li><li>Manage operations on Jurong Island, including manpower planning, safety coordination, and permit processes.</li><li>Ensure proper servicing, troubleshooting, and repair of plant equipment and machinery.</li><li>Provide technical support to clients and internal teams for mechanical, electrical, and civil-related issues.</li><li>Liaise with clients, consultants, subcontractors and vendors to ensure smooth project execution.</li><li>Prepare work reports, quotations, maintenance records and project updates.</li><li>Maintain compliance with safety standards, especially for Jurong Island sites.</li><li>Guide, mentor and train technicians and supervisors.</li><li>Handle any ad-hoc duties assigned by management.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Able to work well with others as a competent team and team leader.</li><li>Able to work flexible hours, night shift and Sundays if required</li><li>Diploma in Mechanical/Electrical & Communication Engineering. Or Degree in Mechanical/Electrical & Communication Engineering.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of relevant experience preferred.</li></ul><ul><li>Knowledge on the tools, equipment, and materials common to the Mechanical & Electrical trade.</li><li>Knowledge on hydraulic & pneumatic system & control.</li><li>Knowledge of applicable electrical codes, standards and regulations.</li><li>Skill in the installation,repair and maintenance of all types of electrical system equipment and components.</li><li>Skill in both verbal and written communication.</li><li>Ability to work independent and self-responsible manner.</li><li>Able to work on an 8 hours rotating shifts.</li><li>Flexible to work on Sundays & Public Holidays.</li><li>Class 3 License Required</li></ul>",
